What is AWS Trusted Advisor?
AWS Trusted Advisor is an online tool that acts as a customized cloud expert. It scans your AWS environment in real-time and provides actionable recommendations to help you follow AWS best practices.

The 6 Pillars (Categories)
Trusted Advisor evaluates your account across these key areas:

üí∞ Cost Optimization: Identifies idle or underutilized resources to save money (e.g., stopping idle EC2 instances).

üöÄ Performance: Checks for service usage limits and provisioned throughput to ensure applications run efficiently.

üîí Security: Detects security vulnerabilities (e.g., S3 buckets with public access, weak IAM passwords).

‚ö†Ô∏è Fault Tolerance: Flags potential single points of failure to increase application redundancy (e.g., no snapshots, single-AZ deployments).

üìà Service Quotas: Alerts you when you are nearing more than 80% of your service limits (e.g., VPC limits, instance limits).

‚öôÔ∏è Operational Excellence: Helps maintain manageable and efficient operations (e.g., identifying resources not managed by Systems Manager).
