What is AWS Control Tower?
AWS Control Tower is a managed service that automates the setup of a secure, multi-account AWS environment. It acts as an orchestration layer on top of AWS Organizations to ensure every account in your company follows the same security and compliance rules.
Scenario: "A company needs to set up a new, secure multi-account environment according to AWS best practices."

üëâ Answer: AWS Control Tower.
What is AWS Security Hub?
AWS Security Hub is a centralized security manager that gives you a comprehensive view of your security alerts and security posture across your AWS accounts. It acts as an aggregator, pulling in data from various AWS security services and third-party tools into a single dashboard.
Scenario: "A security team wants a centralized dashboard to view security alerts from multiple AWS accounts and check if they meet PCI DSS standards."

üëâ Answer: AWS Security Hub.
What is AWS Batch?
AWS Batch is a fully managed service that allows you to run hundreds of thousands of batch computing jobs efficiently. It handles the heavy lifting of provisioning, scheduling, and scaling your compute resources based on the volume of work.
Fully Managed: You don't have to install or manage batch software or server clusters.

Dynamic Scaling: It scales up when the queue is full and scales down to zero when the queue is empty.

Cost Optimization: Natively supports EC2 Spot Instances, allowing you to run batch jobs for up to 90% off regular prices.

Dependency Management: You can set jobs to run only after a previous job completes (e.g., "Don't analyze the data until the download job is finished").
What is AWS Systems Manager (SSM)?
AWS Systems Manager is an operations hub that provides a unified user interface to track, manage, and automate tasks across your AWS resources and on-premises servers. It simplifies the management of "nodes" (EC2 instances, VMs, or edge devices) at scale.
