support plan :-
. Basic Support
Who it's for: All AWS customers automatically.

What you get: 24/7 access to customer service (billing/account issues only) and 7 Core Trusted Advisor checks.

Limitation: No technical support for breaks/fixes.
Developer Support
Who it's for: Non-production workloads.

What you get: Email access to Cloud Support Associates during business hours.

Response Time: < 24 hours (General), < 12 hours (System impaired).

Business+ Support
Who it's for: Running production workloads.

What you get: 24/7 access to Cloud Support Engineers via Email, Chat, and Phone.

Special Features: Full set of Trusted Advisor checks and the AWS Support API for automation.
Enterprise (On-Ramp & Full)
The "White Glove" Service: Designed for large-scale operations.

Technical Account Manager (TAM): Your primary point of contact at AWS who helps with architecture, cost, and reviews.
Concierge Support: A dedicated team to assist with complex billing and account inquiries.

Infrastructure Event Management (IEM): Short-term engagement to help you prepare for big events like a product launch (included in Enterprise, extra fee for Business).


